commit.message: Minor fix for supporting Open Data automated tests
OPEN-3486: Add Service Canada's Invitation Manager
OPEN-3486: Add change file for Service Canada's Invitation Manager

files.patch:
@@ -0,0 +1,7 @@
+Added support for Service Canada's Survey Invitation Manager (https://github.com/ServiceCanada/invitation-manager).
+
+By default this feature is disabled. In order to enable it:
+
+1. Add "IM_ENABLED = True" to the Django project's settings.py file
+2. Extract the contents of the Invitation-manager release to the "search/templates/snippets/im" directory in the project
+3. Configure IM appropriately using the "im.json" and "config.JSON" files.

@@ -18,7 +18,7 @@ utility to execute the entire test suite or individual test files.
 
 ```shell
  > pytest # run all tests
- > pytest test/test_opendata.py
+ > pytest test/test_data.py
 ```
 
 The tests use Django's standard `settings.py` file to determine the URL to search pages.

@@ -328,3 +328,6 @@
 IMPORT_DATA_CSV_BAD_DATA_DIR = os.path.join(BASE_DIR, 'bad_data')
 
 NLTK_DATADIR = os.path.join(BASE_DIR, 'nltk')
+
+# Invitation Manager
+IM_ENABLED = False
@@ -17,7 +17,7 @@ + aria-label="{% translate 'Search text' %}" data-testid="search-text" style="flex: 0.7 0 auto; height: 37px"/>

@@ -0,0 +1,4 @@
+Service Canada Invitation Manager files are installed here. For the
+latest files, please visit:
+
+https://github.com/ServiceCanada/invitation-manager/wiki/Installation-Guide

@@ -300,6 +300,7 @@ def default_context(self, request: HttpRequest, search_type: str, lang: str):
             "mlt_enabled": self.searches[search_type].mlt_enabled,
             "query_path": request.META["QUERY_STRING"],
             "path_info": request.META["PATH_INFO"],
+            "im_enabled": settings.IM_ENABLED if hasattr(settings, 'IM_ENABLED') else False,
         }
         utl_fragments = request.META["PATH_INFO"].split('/')
         utl_fragments = utl_fragments if utl_fragments[-2] == search_type else utl_fragments[:-2]
@@ -599,6 +600,7 @@ def get(self, request: HttpRequest, lang='en', search_type='', record_id=''):
             context["download_ds_url_en"] = self.searches[search_type].dataset_download_url_fr if lang == 'fr' else self.searches[search_type].dataset_download_url_en
             context["search_text"] = request.GET.get("search_text", "")
             context['back_to_url'] = get_search_path(self.searches[search_type], lang)
+            context['im_enabled'] = False
             request.session['prev_record'] = request.build_absolute_uri()
             solr = SolrClient(settings.SOLR_SERVER_URL)
